Vice President Kamala Harris and Secretary of Labor Marty Walsh held a meeting to discuss the importance of protecting workers' ability to engage in collective bargaining. They emphasized the benefits of union membership, such as advocating for wages, benefits, and workplace safety. They highlighted the role of employers in supporting union labor and discussed the positive impact it has on productivity, morale, and worker safety. They also mentioned specific examples, such as the partnership between the UAW and Ford, which has one of the oldest apprenticeship programs. The meeting aimed to strengthen workers' rights and promote a competitive and strong economy.